Authority_Name: The Netherlands - The Dutch Authority for the Financial Markets
Category: Fraud and Other Types of Misconduct
Additional Information: The Netherlands Authority for the Financial Markets (AFM) warns consumers not to respond to offers from LuxNordic. This company is a suspected boiler room, a form of online investment fraud.  LuxNordic has approached persons without being asked, to offer them investment proposals. A boiler room is a collective term for fraudulent individuals and organizations using clever salespeople to call potential investors to pressure them into buying shares that promise high returns (cold calling). In reality the shares are either worthless or non-existent. The AFM has established that  LuxNordic does not have an AFM license or a European Passport.

Authority_Name: The Netherlands - The Dutch Authority for the Financial Markets
Category: Fraud and Other Types of Misconduct
Additional Information: The Netherlands Authority for the Financial Markets (AFM) warns consumers not to respond to offers from Capup. This company is a suspected boiler room, a form of online investment fraud. Capup has approached persons without being asked, to offer them investment proposals. A boiler room is a collective term for fraudulent individuals and organizations using clever salespeople to call potential investors to pressure them into buying shares that promise high returns (cold calling). In reality the shares are either worthless or non-existent. The AFM has established that Capup does not have an AFM license or a European Passport.
